  <Name>k__BackingField: 1 Peter
  fancyName: 
  nickname: 1pe
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: dd64eb842f3dd694bae8487ce6510215, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greeting'
      title: Greeting
      number: 1
      content: '  Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ,To those who are elect exiles
        of the Dispersion in Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Born Again to a Living Hope'
      title: Born Again to a Living Hope
      number: 2
      content: 'according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, in the sanctification
        of the Spirit, for obedience to Jesus Christ and for sprinkling with his
        blood:May grace and peace be multiplied to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: '  Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ! According
        to his great mercy, he has caused us to be born again to a living hope through
        the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'to an inheritance that is imperishable, undefiled, and unfading,
        kept in heaven for you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "who by God\u2019s power are being guarded through faith for a salvation
        ready to be revealed in the last time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'In this you rejoice, though now for a little while, if necessary,
        you have been grieved by various trials, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "so that the tested genuineness of your faith\u2014more precious than
        gold that perishes though it is tested by fire\u2014may be found to result
        in praise and glory and honor at the revelation of Jesus Christ. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Though you have not seen him, you love him. Though you do not now
        see him, you believe in him and rejoice with joy that is inexpressible and
        filled with glory, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'obtaining the outcome of your faith, the salvation of your souls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Concerning this salvation, the prophets who prophesied about the
        grace that was to be yours searched and inquired carefully, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'inquiring what person or time[[COMMENT(0)]]  the Spirit of Christ
        in them was indicating when he predicted the sufferings of Christ and the
        subsequent glories. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '12: Called to Be Holy'
      title: Called to Be Holy
      number: 12
      content: 'It was revealed to them that they were serving not themselves but
        you, in the things that have now been announced to you through those who
        preached the good news to you by the Holy Spirit sent from heaven, things
        into which angels long to look.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore, preparing your minds for action,[[COMMENT(0)]] and being
        sober-minded, set your hope fully on the grace that will be brought to you
        at the revelation of Jesus Christ. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'As obedient children, do not be conformed to the passions of your
        former ignorance, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but as he who called you is holy, you also be holy in all your conduct, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "since it is written, \u201CYou shall be holy, for I am holy.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And if you call on him as Father who judges impartially according
        to each one\u2019s deeds, conduct yourselves with fear throughout the time
        of your exile, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'knowing that you were ransomed from the futile ways inherited from
        your forefathers, not with perishable things such as silver or gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'but with the precious blood of Christ, like that of a lamb without
        blemish or spot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He was foreknown before the foundation of the world but was made
        manifest in the last times for the sake of you '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'who through him are believers in God, who raised him from the dead
        and gave him glory, so that your faith and hope are in God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Having purified your souls by your obedience to the truth for a sincere
        brotherly love, love one another earnestly from a pure heart, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'since you have been born again, not of perishable seed but of imperishable,
        through the living and abiding word of God; '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "for  \u201CAll flesh is like grassand all its glory like the flower
        of grass.The grass withers,and the flower falls,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "  but the word of the Lord remains forever.\u201DAnd this word is
        the good news that was preached to you."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Living Stone and a Holy People'
      title: A Living Stone and a Holy People
      number: 1
      content: '    So put away all malice and all deceit and hypocrisy and envy
        and all slander. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Like newborn infants, long for the pure spiritual milk, that by it
        you may grow up into salvation\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'if indeed you have tasted that the Lord is good.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'As you come to him, a living stone rejected by men but in the sight
        of God chosen and precious, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'you yourselves like living stones are being built up as a spiritual
        house, to be a holy priesthood, to offer spiritual sacrifices acceptable
        to God through Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For it stands in Scripture:  \u201CBehold, I am laying in Zion a
        stone,a cornerstone chosen and precious,  and whoever believes in him will
        not be put to shame.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the honor is for you who believe, but for those who do not believe, 
        \u201CThe stone that the builders rejectedhas become the cornerstone,\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and  \u201CA stone of stumbling,and a rock of offense.\u201DThey
        stumble because they disobey the word, as they were destined to do.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people
        for his own possession, that you may proclaim the excellencies of him who
        called you out of darkness into his marvelous light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Once you were not a people, but now you are God\u2019s people; once
        you had not received mercy, but now you have received mercy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Beloved, I urge you as sojourners and exiles to abstain from the
        passions of the flesh, which wage war against your soul. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Submission to Authority'
      title: Submission to Authority
      number: 12
      content: 'Keep your conduct among the Gentiles honorable, so that when they
        speak against you as evildoers, they may see your good deeds and glorify
        God on the day of visitation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "  Be subject for the Lord\u2019s sake to every human institution,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        whether it be to the emperor as supreme, "
      comments:
      - number: '2:13 '
        content: Or Or ; also verse 17
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'or to governors as sent by him to punish those who do evil and to
        praise those who do good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For this is the will of God, that by doing good you should put to
        silence the ignorance of foolish people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Live as people who are free, not using your freedom as a cover-up
        for evil, but living as servants[[COMMENT(0)]] of God. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:16 '
        content: For the contextual rendering of the Greek word , see Preface
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Honor everyone. Love the brotherhood. Fear God. Honor the emperor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: '  Servants, be subject to your masters with all respect, not only
        to the good and gentle but also to the unjust. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For this is a gracious thing, when, mindful of God, one endures sorrows
        while suffering unjustly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For what credit is it if, when you sin and are beaten for it, you
        endure? But if when you do good and suffer for it you endure, this is a gracious
        thing in the sight of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For to this you have been called, because Christ also suffered for
        you, leaving you an example, so that you might follow in his steps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'He committed no sin, neither was deceit found in his mouth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'When he was reviled, he did not revile in return; when he suffered,
        he did not threaten, but continued entrusting himself to him who judges justly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He himself bore our sins in his body on the tree, that we might die
        to sin and live to righteousness. By his wounds you have been healed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: For you were straying like sheep, but have now returned to the Shepherd
        and Overseer of your souls.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Wives and Husbands'
      title: Wives and Husbands
      number: 1
      content: '  Likewise, wives, be subject to your own husbands, so that even
        if some do not obey the word, they may be won without a word by the conduct
        of their wives, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'when they see your respectful and pure conduct. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Do not let your adorning be external\u2014the braiding of hair and
        the putting on of gold jewelry, or the clothing you wear\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "but let your adorning be the hidden person of the heart with the
        imperishable beauty of a gentle and quiet spirit, which in God\u2019s sight
        is very precious. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For this is how the holy women who hoped in God used to adorn themselves,
        by submitting to their own husbands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'as Sarah obeyed Abraham, calling him lord. And you are her children,
        if you do good and do not fear anything that is frightening.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Suffering for Righteousness\u2019 Sake"
      title: "Suffering for Righteousness\u2019 Sake"
      number: 7
      content: 'Likewise, husbands, live with your wives in an understanding way,
        showing honor to the woman as the weaker vessel, since they are heirs with
        you[[COMMENT(0)]] of the grace of life, so that your prayers may not be hindered.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Finally, all of you, have unity of mind, sympathy, brotherly love,
        a tender heart, and a humble mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not repay evil for evil or reviling for reviling, but on the contrary,
        bless, for to this you were called, that you may obtain a blessing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For  \u201CWhoever desires to love lifeand see good days,let him
        keep his tongue from eviland his lips from speaking deceit;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'let him turn away from evil and do good;let him seek peace and pursue
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For the eyes of the Lord are on the righteous,and his ears are open
        to their prayer.But the face of the Lord is against those who do evil.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now who is there to harm you if you are zealous for what is good? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But even if you should suffer for righteousness\u2019 sake, you will
        be blessed. Have no fear of them, nor be troubled, "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'but in your hearts honor Christ the Lord as holy, always being prepared
        to make a defense to anyone who asks you for a reason for the hope that is
        in you; yet do it with gentleness and respect, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'having a good conscience, so that, when you are slandered, those
        who revile your good behavior in Christ may be put to shame. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For it is better to suffer for doing good, if that should be God\u2019s
        will, than for doing evil.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For Christ also suffered[[COMMENT(0)]]  once for sins, the righteous
        for the unrighteous, that he might bring us to God, being put to death in
        the flesh but made alive in the spirit, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:18 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'in which[[COMMENT(0)]] he went and proclaimed to the spirits in prison, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:19 '
        content: 'Or Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "because[[COMMENT(0)]] they formerly did not obey, when God\u2019s
        patience waited in the days of Noah, while the ark was being prepared, in
        which a few, that is, eight persons, were brought safely through water. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:20 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Baptism, which corresponds to this, now saves you, not as a removal
        of dirt from the body but as an appeal to God for a good conscience, through
        the resurrection of Jesus Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: who has gone into heaven and is at the right hand of God, with angels,
        authorities, and powers having been subjected to him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Stewards of God\u2019s Grace"
      title: "Stewards of God\u2019s Grace"
      number: 1
      content: '  Since therefore Christ suffered in the flesh,[[COMMENT(0)]]  arm
        yourselves with the same way of thinking, for whoever has suffered in the
        flesh has ceased from sin, '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts add ; some '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'so as to live for the rest of the time in the flesh no longer for
        human passions but for the will of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the time that is past suffices for doing what the Gentiles want
        to do, living in sensuality, passions, drunkenness, orgies, drinking parties,
        and lawless idolatry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'With respect to this they are surprised when you do not join them
        in the same flood of debauchery, and they malign you; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'but they will give account to him who is ready to judge the living
        and the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For this is why the gospel was preached even to those who are dead,
        that though judged in the flesh the way people are, they might live in the
        spirit the way God does.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: '  The end of all things is at hand; therefore be self-controlled
        and sober-minded for the sake of your prayers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Above all, keep loving one another earnestly, since love covers a
        multitude of sins. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Show hospitality to one another without grumbling. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As each has received a gift, use it to serve one another, as good
        stewards of God\u2019s varied grace: "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Suffering as a Christian'
      title: Suffering as a Christian
      number: 11
      content: "whoever speaks, as one who speaks oracles of God; whoever serves,
        as one who serves by the strength that God supplies\u2014in order that in
        everything God may be glorified through Jesus Christ. To him belong glory
        and dominion forever and ever. Amen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Beloved, do not be surprised at the fiery trial when it comes upon
        you to test you, as though something strange were happening to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But rejoice insofar as you share Christ\u2019s sufferings, that you
        may also rejoice and be glad when his glory is revealed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'If you are insulted for the name of Christ, you are blessed, because
        the Spirit of glory[[COMMENT(0)]] and of God rests upon you. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:14 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts insert '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But let none of you suffer as a murderer or a thief or an evildoer
        or as a meddler. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Yet if anyone suffers as a Christian, let him not be ashamed, but
        let him glorify God in that name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For it is time for judgment to begin at the household of God; and
        if it begins with us, what will be the outcome for those who do not obey
        the gospel of God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And  \u201CIf the righteous is scarcely saved,what will become of
        the ungodly and the sinner?\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:18 '
        content: 'Greek '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Therefore let those who suffer according to God\u2019s will entrust
        their souls to a faithful Creator while doing good."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Shepherd the Flock of God'
      title: Shepherd the Flock of God
      number: 1
      content: '  So I exhort the elders among you, as a fellow elder and a witness
        of the sufferings of Christ, as well as a partaker in the glory that is going
        to be revealed: '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'shepherd the flock of God that is among you, exercising oversight,[[COMMENT(0)]] 
        not under compulsion, but willingly, as God would have you;  not for shameful
        gain, but eagerly; '
      comments:
      - number: '5:2 '
        content: 'Some manuscripts omit Some manuscripts omit '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'not domineering over those in your charge, but being examples to
        the flock. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when the chief Shepherd appears, you will receive the unfading
        crown of glory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Likewise, you who are younger, be subject to the elders. Clothe yourselves,
        all of you, with humility toward one another, for \u201CGod opposes the proud
        but gives grace to the humble.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  Humble yourselves, therefore, under the mighty hand of God so that
        at the proper time he may exalt you, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'casting all your anxieties on him, because he cares for you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Be sober-minded; be watchful. Your adversary the devil prowls around
        like a roaring lion, seeking someone to devour. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Resist him, firm in your faith, knowing that the same kinds of suffering
        are being experienced by your brotherhood throughout the world. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And after you have suffered a little while, the God of all grace,
        who has called you to his eternal glory in Christ, will himself restore,
        confirm, strengthen, and establish you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Final Greetings'
      title: Final Greetings
      number: 11
      content: 'To him be the dominion forever and ever. Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'By Silvanus, a faithful brother as I regard him, I have written briefly
        to you, exhorting and declaring that this is the true grace of God. Stand
        firm in it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'She who is at Babylon, who is likewise chosen, sends you greetings,
        and so does Mark, my son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Greet one another with the kiss of love.  Peace to all of you who
        are in Christ.
      comments: []
